{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"AC1 VERIFIED STATEMENT (g2p branch filtering) — with a MAJOR discovered gap:\n\ng2p does NOT branch-filter dispatch. patchset-created on ANY branch (incl. feature/*) dispatches the mapped 'verify' workflow; the event->workflow mapping is filename-substring based (filter_path requires 'verify'+'gerrit' in the workflow filename), NOT branch-scoped. gerrit_to_platform.ini has NO [filters]/branch keys — only [mapping \"comment-added\"]. So NO g2p config is needed for feature/*.\nSource (lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform @44d5d46): patchset_created.py:31-118 (unconditional find_and_dispatch(project,'verify',inputs)), github.py:78-149 (filter_workflows/filter_path branch-agnostic), helpers.py get_change_refspec:278-291.\n\n** GAP (the exact failure S3 exists to catch): ** g2p dispatches via GitHub workflow_dispatch with ref = refs/heads/{GERRIT_BRANCH} (helpers.py dispatch block; github.py:25-53 dispatch_workflow). workflow_dispatch REQUIRES that ref to exist on the GitHub mirror. But replication.config pushes ONLY refs/heads/main + refs/tags/* + refs/changes/* — NOT refs/heads/feature/*. So a feature/* change's dispatch targets a non-existent GitHub ref -> 422/no-op -> NO CI run -> NO Verified -> the story change on the feature branch can never satisfy the two-vote gate and can never be submitted. LLM-Review would still be cast (bot is branch-agnostic); Verified would silently never arrive. This is 'story changes never earn Verified and every submit blocks with no error signal' verbatim.\n\nNote: the code-under-test IS available on GitHub for feature changes (refs/changes/* IS replicated, and checkout-gerrit-change-action fetches GERRIT_REFSPEC) — the ONLY missing piece is the workflow-file ref for the dispatch. get_change_refspec computes refs/changes/NN/NNNN/P identically for merge and normal commits (no special merge handling), so a merge change's patchset ref (the merge tree) is what CI checks out — good for AC3.\n\nFIX (candidate): add push = refs/heads/feature/*:refs/heads/feature/* to replication.config so the dispatch ref resolves. Confirming the gap empirically next, then applying + re-verifying."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783060900392754001,"uuid":"7bb129b8-7926-4560-9d3b-4a49978e9e6d"}